description: Deno + Pylon GraphQL API conventions for apps/timemanager-api (Kysely + Postgres).
globs: apps/timemanager-api/**
---

`apps/timemanager-api` is a **Deno** app (Pylon GraphQL) — use `deno.json` tasks, NOT Node, Bun, npm, or pnpm here. Dependencies are declared in `deno.json` `imports`.

Stack: [Pylon](https://pylon.cronit.io/) (`@getcronit/pylon`) for GraphQL, [Kysely](https://kysely.dev/) query builder over Postgres (`pg`). Serves on `:3000`.

Source layout (`src/`):

- `index.ts` — entrypoint + auth middleware (Bearer JWT → local `userId`).
- `auth/verify.ts` — SuperTokens JWKS JWT verification (`jose`).
- `graphql/` — `types.ts`, `resolvers/resolvers.ts` (user id from `getContext()`, not client input).
- `db/` — `database.ts`, `users.ts` (upsert by `auth_user_id`), `types/schema.ts`, `migrations/`, `seed.ts`.

Auth: every `/graphql` request requires `Authorization: Bearer <SuperTokens access token>`. JWKS is loaded from `AUTH_API_DOMAIN` (default `http://localhost:3001`) at `/auth/jwt/jwks.json`. Local users are linked via `users.auth_user_id`. Postgres comes from `DATABASE_URL` or `PG*` env vars (defaults match local docker-compose). Public `GET /health` is unauthenticated for ALB checks.

Commands (via `deno task`, or the Nx wrappers `nx serve|build|run timemanager-api`):

- `deno task dev` — dev server (Nx `serve` / `pnpm timemanager`, which also runs `migrate` → DB and starts `user-manager-api`).
- `deno task build` — build.
- `deno task migrate` — apply pending Kysely migrations (`nx run timemanager-api:migrate`).
- `deno task seed` — seed the DB (`nx run timemanager-api:seed`).

The database comes from `infra/timemanager-db` (Postgres `:5432`). `pnpm db:up` starts it and runs migrations.
